        <h2 class="section-h2">Frequently Asked Questions About Living Abroad</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Are the tools on this site free to use? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes, completely free. All four tools — the Salary Arbitrage tool, Country Match quiz, Retire Abroad planner, and Expat Tax Guide — require no account, no signup, and no payment. We cover operating costs through affiliate commissions if you choose to use one of our partner links, at no extra cost to you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Where does the data come from and how accurate is it? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Every number on this site comes from a publicly available, independently maintained source. Purchasing power data comes from the World Bank. US city prices come from the Bureau of Economic Analysis. Quality of life scores draw on Numbeo, the World Happiness Report, Speedtest Global Index, and the EF English Proficiency Index. Cost of living budgets come from the WhereNext API. Results reflect standardized economic data from authoritative sources. Actual costs vary by city, lifestyle, and personal circumstances.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">How does the Country Match quiz work? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>The quiz asks 10 questions about your priorities: monthly budget, climate preference, healthcare needs, language comfort, remote work situation, interest in nomad visas, safety requirements, family situation, cultural openness, and lifestyle pace. Each answer adjusts how 82 countries are scored against your profile. The result is a ranked list showing which countries fit your specific situation and why, not a generic popularity ranking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Does the salary tool account for taxes? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>The Salary Arbitrage tool shows gross purchasing power based on PPP data and does not factor in taxes. US citizens must file a federal tax return every year regardless of where they live, though the Foreign Earned Income Exclusion (FEIE) may reduce or eliminate US tax liability on foreign-earned income up to a threshold. For a full breakdown of how expat taxes work, see our <a href="/taxes">Expat Tax Guide</a>. State tax obligations vary and are also covered there.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I use this site to plan early retirement abroad? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes. The <a href="/fire">Retire Abroad tool</a> is built specifically for Americans pursuing financial independence or early retirement. Enter your savings and a withdrawal rate (the standard starting point is 4%), and the tool shows how far your portfolio goes in 74 countries with real cost of living data. Many countries where your savings fall short in the US become fully viable abroad.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Do I need a visa to move to these countries? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Americans can visit most countries visa-free for 30 to 90 days on a US passport. Long-term residency requires a separate visa or residence permit. Many countries now offer digital nomad visas specifically for remote workers earning income outside the country. Visa requirements, processing times, and income thresholds vary by country. Each country page on this site shows the visa-free days available on a US passport and whether a digital nomad visa program exists.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Which countries offer digital nomad visas? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Over 50 countries now offer some form of digital nomad visa or remote work permit for foreigners earning income outside the country. Popular options include Portugal, Spain, Greece, Germany, Costa Rica, Panama, Georgia, and Thailand. Each program has its own income requirements, application process, and permitted stay duration. Every country page on this site shows whether a nomad visa program is available, and the <a href="/countries/goals/digital-nomad-visas">Digital Nomad Visas list</a> ranks all eligible countries in one place.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can I collect Social Security while living abroad? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>In most cases, yes. US citizens living abroad can generally collect Social Security retirement benefits, with payments sent directly to a foreign bank account or a US account. There are exceptions for a small number of countries where the Social Security Administration does not send payments. Medicare does not cover medical care outside the United States. Check the SSA official guidance and consult a financial advisor familiar with expat retirement planning before making decisions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What is Purchasing Power Parity? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Purchasing power parity is an economic measure that compares how much a given amount of money buys in different countries. A multiplier of 2x means your dollar buys twice as much locally as it does in the US. We use World Bank PPP data combined with BEA regional price data to estimate how far your specific US city salary stretches in each destination country.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can Americans keep US citizenship if they move abroad? <span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Yes. Moving abroad does not affect US citizenship. Americans can live in another country indefinitely while keeping full US citizenship, including the right to vote in federal elections, hold a US passport, and return to the United States at any time. Renouncing citizenship is a separate, irreversible legal process that requires deliberate action at a US consulate.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 9: FOOTER -->

</BaseLayout>

<script id="quality-data" type="application/json" set:html={JSON.stringify(qualityScores.countries)} />
<script id="city-rpp-data" type="application/json" set:html={JSON.stringify(cityRpp.cities)} />

<script>
  const QUALITY = JSON.parse(
    document.getElementById('quality-data')!.textContent!
  );
  const CITY_RPP = JSON.parse(
    document.getElementById('city-rpp-data')!.textContent!
  );

  const COUNTRY_SLUGS: Record<string, string> = {
    "PT": "portugal",  "ES": "spain",       "MX": "mexico",
    "DE": "germany",   "IT": "italy",        "GR": "greece",
    "CR": "costa-rica","PA": "panama",       "TH": "thailand",
    "MY": "malaysia",  "ID": "indonesia",    "CO": "colombia",
    "HR": "croatia",   "CZ": "czech-republic","PL": "poland",
    "HU": "hungary",   "RO": "romania",      "BG": "bulgaria",
    "VN": "vietnam",   "JP": "japan",        "KR": "south-korea",
    "AU": "australia", "NZ": "new-zealand",  "CA": "canada",
    "IE": "ireland",   "NL": "netherlands",  "FR": "france",
    "AR": "argentina", "EC": "ecuador",      "MA": "morocco",
    "AL": "albania",   "AT": "austria",      "BE": "belgium",
    "BR": "brazil",    "CL": "chile",        "CN": "china",
    "DK": "denmark",   "EG": "egypt",        "FI": "finland",
    "GE": "georgia",   "IS": "iceland",      "IN": "india",
    "KE": "kenya",     "NO": "norway",       "PE": "peru",
    "PH": "philippines","QA": "qatar",       "SA": "saudi-arabia",
    "RS": "serbia",    "SG": "singapore",    "LK": "sri-lanka",
    "SE": "sweden",    "CH": "switzerland",  "AE": "united-arab-emirates",
    "GB": "united-kingdom",
    "BS": "bahamas",    "BZ": "belize",        "BO": "bolivia",
    "KH": "cambodia",  "CY": "cyprus",        "DO": "dominican-republic",
    "SV": "el-salvador","EE": "estonia",       "GH": "ghana",
    "HN": "honduras",  "JM": "jamaica",       "KZ": "kazakhstan",
    "LV": "latvia",    "LT": "lithuania",     "MT": "malta",
    "ME": "montenegro","NP": "nepal",         "NI": "nicaragua",
    "MK": "north-macedonia","PY": "paraguay", "RW": "rwanda",
    "SK": "slovakia",  "SI": "slovenia",      "ZA": "south-africa",
    "TW": "taiwan",    "TR": "turkey",        "UY": "uruguay",
  };

  const citySelect    = document.getElementById('citySelect');
  const incomeInput   = document.getElementById('incomeInput');
  const remoteCheck   = document.getElementById('remoteCheck');
  const countrySelect = document.getElementById('countrySelect');
  const calcBtn       = document.getElementById('calcBtn');
  const loadingState      = document.getElementById('loadingState');
  const errorState        = document.getElementById('errorState');
  const resultsEmpty      = document.getElementById('resultsEmpty');
  const resultsData       = document.getElementById('resultsData');
  const annualSavingsEl   = document.getElementById('annualSavings');
  const monthlySavingsEl  = document.getElementById('monthlySavings');
  const purchasingPowerEl    = document.getElementById('purchasingPower');
  const purchasingPowerSubEl = document.getElementById('purchasingPowerSub');
  const yearsToFireEl     = document.getElementById('yearsToFire');
  const shareBtn      = document.getElementById('shareBtn');
  const copyBtn       = document.getElementById('copyBtn');

  // Prefill country from Country Match quiz
  // or country pages, if present
  (function() {
    const prefillCountry = sessionStorage.getItem(
      'quiz_country'
    );
    if (!prefillCountry) return;

    const countrySelectEl = document.getElementById(
      'countrySelect'
    );
    if (!countrySelectEl) return;

    // countrySelect options are keyed by ISO2
    // code — find the matching ISO2 via COUNTRY_SLUGS
    let matchedIso2 = null;
    for (const [iso2, slug] of Object.entries(
      COUNTRY_SLUGS
    )) {
      if (slug === prefillCountry) {
        matchedIso2 = iso2;
        break;
      }
    }

    if (matchedIso2) {
      (countrySelectEl as HTMLSelectElement).value = matchedIso2;
    }

    // Clear so it doesn't persist on future visits
    sessionStorage.removeItem('quiz_country');

    // Scroll to calculator after page has settled
    setTimeout(() => {
      const calcSection = document.getElementById('salary-arbitrage');
      if (calcSection) {
        calcSection.scrollIntoView({
          behavior: 'smooth'
        });
      }
    }, 300);
  })();

  function getCached(key) {
    try {
      const item = localStorage.getItem(key);
      if (!item) return null;
      const { value, expires } = JSON.parse(item);
      if (Date.now() > expires) {
        localStorage.removeItem(key);
        return null;
      }
      return value;
    } catch { return null; }
  }

  function setCache(key, value, ttlMs) {
    try {
      localStorage.setItem(key, JSON.stringify({
        value,
        expires: Date.now() + ttlMs
      }));
    } catch {}
  }

  function calculateOverallScore(quality) {
    const weights = {
      safety: 0.25,
      healthcare: 0.20,
      happiness: 0.15,
      hdi: 0.15,
      pollution: 0.08,
      unemployment: 0.07,
      internet: 0.05,
      traffic: 0.05
    };

    let totalScore = 0;
    let totalWeight = 0;

    for (const [metric, weight] of Object.entries(weights)) {
      const score = quality[metric];
      if (score !== null && score !== undefined) {
        totalScore += score * weight;
        totalWeight += weight;
      }
    }

    const weightedAverage = totalWeight > 0 ? totalScore / totalWeight : 0;
    const percent = Math.round(weightedAverage * 10);

    let verdict;
    if (percent >= 90) verdict = 'Outstanding destination';
    else if (percent >= 80) verdict = 'Excellent destination';
    else if (percent >= 70) verdict = 'Very good destination';
    else if (percent >= 60) verdict = 'Good destination';
    else if (percent >= 50) verdict = 'Moderate destination';
    else if (percent >= 40) verdict = 'Mixed destination';
    else if (percent >= 30) verdict = 'Limited destination';
    else verdict = 'Challenging destination';

    return { percent, verdict };
  }

  function animateCounter(element, target, duration) {
    const increment = target / (duration / 16);
    let current = 0;
    const timer = setInterval(() => {
      current += increment;
      if (current >= target) {
        current = target;
        clearInterval(timer);
      }
      element.textContent = '$' + Math.round(current).toLocaleString();
    }, 16);
  }

  calcBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const cityId   = citySelect.value;
    const income   = parseInt(incomeInput.value);
    const isRemote = remoteCheck.checked;
    const iso2     = countrySelect.value;

    if (!cityId || !income || !iso2) {
      alert('Please fill in all fields');
      return;
    }
    if (income < 15000 || income > 1000000) {
      alert('Please enter income between $15,000 and $1,000,000');
      return;
    }

    loadingState.style.display = 'block';
    resultsEmpty.style.display = 'none';
    errorState.style.display   = 'none';
    calcBtn.disabled           = true;

    const COUNTRY_CURRENCIES = {
      "PT":"EUR","ES":"EUR","MX":"MXN","DE":"EUR",
      "IT":"EUR","GR":"EUR","CR":"CRC","PA":"USD",
      "TH":"THB","MY":"MYR","ID":"IDR","CO":"COP",
      "HR":"EUR","CZ":"CZK","PL":"PLN","HU":"HUF",
      "RO":"RON","BG":"BGN","VN":"VND","JP":"JPY",
      "KR":"KRW","AU":"AUD","NZ":"NZD","CA":"CAD",
      "IE":"EUR","NL":"EUR","FR":"EUR","AR":"ARS",
      "EC":"USD","MA":"MAD",
      "AL":"ALL","AT":"EUR","BE":"EUR","BR":"BRL",
      "CL":"CLP","CN":"CNY","DK":"DKK","EG":"EGP",
      "FI":"EUR","GE":"GEL","IS":"ISK","IN":"INR",
      "KE":"KES","NO":"NOK","PE":"PEN","PH":"PHP",
      "QA":"QAR","SA":"SAR","RS":"RSD","SG":"SGD",
      "LK":"LKR","SE":"SEK","CH":"CHF","AE":"AED",
      "GB":"GBP",
      "BS":"BSD","BZ":"BZD","BO":"BOB","KH":"KHR",
      "CY":"EUR","DO":"DOP","SV":"USD","EE":"EUR",
      "GH":"GHS","HN":"HNL","JM":"JMD","KZ":"KZT",
      "LV":"EUR","LT":"EUR","MT":"EUR","ME":"EUR",
      "NP":"NPR","NI":"NIO","MK":"MKD","PY":"PYG",
      "RW":"RWF","SK":"EUR","SI":"EUR","ZA":"ZAR",
      "TW":"TWD","TR":"TRY","UY":"UYU",
    };

    // Static PPP values (World Bank PA.NUS.PRVT.PP, fetched 2026-06-23)
    // Eliminates runtime WB API calls — update quarterly by running scripts/fetch-ppp-embed.py
    const STATIC_PPP: Record<string, number> = {
      "PT":0.5587,"ES":0.5885,"PL":2.008,"MX":10.8013,"TH":11.7121,
      "DE":0.7015,"JP":99.3848,"HR":0.494,"CZ":14.3264,"HU":189.3142,
      "RO":2.0566,"BG":0.7627,"VN":7160.7129,"KR":872.4687,"AU":1.4274,
      "NZ":1.4999,"CA":1.2409,"IE":0.882,"NL":0.7419,"FR":0.7169,
      "AR":42.9862,"EC":0.4415,"MA":3.9596,"CH":1.1072,"NO":9.5401,
      "DK":6.7644,"SE":8.5776,"BE":0.7522,"AT":0.7205,"FI":0.7882,
      "GB":0.6827,"SG":1.0238,"AE":2.5631,"QA":2.7555,"SA":1.8711,
      "IS":156.0262,"IN":19.8004,"PH":20.5335,"CN":3.4596,"GE":1.0875,
      "RS":50.5842,"KE":44.9843,"PE":1.927,"BR":2.5815,"CL":464.876,
      "AL":45.8631,"LK":81.1323,"EG":7.7218,"ID":5065.969,"CO":1542.1938,
      "CR":328.0466,"PA":0.5111,"MY":1.4306,"IT":0.6252,"GR":0.5578,
      "BS":1.1068,"BZ":1.0876,"BO":2.6992,"KH":1477.7937,"CY":0.5908,
      "DO":23.8085,"SV":0.4688,"EE":0.6461,"GH":4.721,"HN":12.617,
      "JM":98.2417,"KZ":190.9828,"LV":0.5331,"LT":0.5265,"MT":0.5839,
      "ME":0.4139,"NP":35.2703,"NI":13.5338,"MK":21.463,"PY":2874.5596,
      "RW":372.7081,"SK":0.5453,"SI":0.5771,"ZA":7.74,"TW":15.0,
      "TR":12.5517,"UY":29.8551,
    };

    try {
      const currency    = COUNTRY_CURRENCIES[iso2];
      const cityRPP     = CITY_RPP[cityId];
      const countryName = countrySelect.options[countrySelect.selectedIndex].text;
      const cityName    = citySelect.options[citySelect.selectedIndex].text;

      const fxCacheKey = 'fx_usd';

      // PPP: use static embedded values — no API call needed
      const countryPPP = STATIC_PPP[iso2];
      if (!countryPPP) throw new Error(`No PPP data for ${iso2}`);

      let exchangeRate = getCached(fxCacheKey + '_' + currency);
      if (!exchangeRate && currency !== 'USD') {
        exchangeRate = await fetch('https://open.er-api.com/v6/latest/USD')
          .then(r => r.json())
          .then(data => {
            const rates = data.rates;
            Object.entries(rates).forEach(([cur, rate]) => {
              setCache(fxCacheKey + '_' + cur, rate, 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000);
            });
            return rates[currency];
          });
        if (!exchangeRate) throw new Error('No exchange rate for ' + currency);
      } else if (currency === 'USD') {
        exchangeRate = 1;
      }

      const priceLevel       = countryPPP / exchangeRate;
      const adjustedMultiplier = (1 / priceLevel) * cityRPP;
      const equivalentIncome  = Math.round(income / adjustedMultiplier);

      let annualSavings  = 0;
      let monthlySavings = 0;
      if (isRemote) {
        annualSavings  = income - equivalentIncome;
        monthlySavings = Math.round(annualSavings / 12);
      }

      const fireTarget     = equivalentIncome * 25;
      const yearsToFireNum = (isRemote && annualSavings > 0)
        ? Math.round(fireTarget / annualSavings)
        : null;

      if (isRemote && annualSavings > 0) {
        annualSavingsEl.style.color  = '#16A34A';
        monthlySavingsEl.textContent = 'You save $' + monthlySavings.toLocaleString() + '/month';
        animateCounter(annualSavingsEl, annualSavings, 600);
      } else if (isRemote && annualSavings <= 0) {
        annualSavingsEl.textContent  = 'Higher cost';
        annualSavingsEl.style.color  = '#DC2626';
        monthlySavingsEl.textContent = 'Cost of living exceeds ' + cityName;
      } else {
        annualSavingsEl.textContent  = '$' + equivalentIncome.toLocaleString();
        annualSavingsEl.style.color  = '#2563EB';
        monthlySavingsEl.textContent = 'Equivalent income needed in ' + countryName;
      }
      document.getElementById('savingsDesc').textContent = `Money you keep every year by living in ${countryName} instead of ${cityName}`;

      purchasingPowerEl.textContent    = adjustedMultiplier.toFixed(2) + 'x';
      purchasingPowerSubEl.textContent = '$' + income.toLocaleString() + ' → $' + Math.round(income * adjustedMultiplier).toLocaleString() + ' in ' + countryName;
      document.getElementById('powerDesc').textContent = `Your dollar goes ${adjustedMultiplier.toFixed(1)}x further. Your lifestyle costs that much less.`;

      if (!isRemote) {
        yearsToFireEl.textContent = 'Enable remote income to calculate';
      } else if (annualSavings <= 0) {
        yearsToFireEl.textContent = 'Costs more than your origin city';
      } else if (yearsToFireNum) {
        yearsToFireEl.textContent = yearsToFireNum + ' years';
      } else {
        yearsToFireEl.textContent = 'N/A';
      }
      document.getElementById('fireDesc').textContent = isRemote && annualSavings > 0 && yearsToFireNum <= 100
        ? `Build enough wealth to retire in ${countryName} in ${yearsToFireNum} years`
        : `Based on 4% safe withdrawal rate (FIRE method)`;

      const slug = COUNTRY_SLUGS[iso2];
      const q    = QUALITY[slug];

      const overallScore = (q.grade_percent != null && q.grade_label)
        ? { percent: q.grade_percent, verdict: q.grade_label }
        : calculateOverallScore(q);

      document.getElementById('scoreVerdict').textContent = overallScore.verdict;
      document.getElementById('scoreDesc').textContent    = `Rated across 8 quality-of-life metrics weighted for American expats relocating abroad`;

      (function animateCalcGauge(percent) {
        const ARC_LENGTH = 267;
        const arc    = document.getElementById('calcGaugeArc');
        const needle = document.getElementById('calcGaugeNeedle');
        const numEl  = document.getElementById('scorePercentNumber');

        const filledLength  = (percent / 100) * ARC_LENGTH;
        const targetAngle   = (percent / 100) * 180 - 90;
        const startAngle    = -90;
        const duration      = 1300;

        // Arc: CSS transition handles it — just set the final value
        requestAnimationFrame(() => {
          requestAnimationFrame(() => {
            if (arc) arc.style.strokeDashoffset = String(ARC_LENGTH - filledLength);
          });
        });

        // Needle: manual rAF loop, same easeOutBack as Gauge.astro
        if (needle) {
          function easeOutBack(t) {
            const c1 = 1.5, c3 = c1 + 1;
            return 1 + c3 * Math.pow(t - 1, 3) + c1 * Math.pow(t - 1, 2);
          }
          const needleStart = performance.now();
          function animateNeedle(now) {
            const t = Math.min((now - needleStart) / duration, 1);
            const angle = startAngle + (targetAngle - startAngle) * easeOutBack(t);
            needle.setAttribute('transform', `rotate(${angle}, 100, 105)`);
            if (t < 1) requestAnimationFrame(animateNeedle);
          }
          requestAnimationFrame(animateNeedle);
        }

        // Count-up with easeOutExpo
        if (numEl) {
          const numStart = performance.now();
          function tick(now) {
            const t = Math.min((now - numStart) / duration, 1);
            const eased = t === 1 ? 1 : 1 - Math.pow(2, -10 * t);
            numEl.textContent = String(Math.round(eased * percent));
            if (t < 1) requestAnimationFrame(tick);
          }
          requestAnimationFrame(tick);
        }

        const percentEl = document.getElementById('scorePercent');
        if (percentEl) {
          const color = percent >= 70 ? '#16A34A' : percent >= 50 ? '#D97706' : '#DC2626';
          percentEl.style.color = color;
        }
      })(overallScore.percent);

      const metrics = [
        ['safety',       'safetyScore',    'safetyBar'],
        ['healthcare',   'healthScore',    'healthBar'],
        ['happiness',    'happinessScore', 'happinessBar'],
        ['pollution',    'pollutionScore', 'pollutionBar'],
        ['internet',     'internetScore',  'internetBar'],
        ['traffic',      'trafficScore',   'trafficBar'],
        ['unemployment', 'unempScore',     'unempBar'],
        ['hdi',          'hdiScore',       'hdiBar']
      ];

      metrics.forEach(([key, scoreId, barId]) => {
        const val = q[key];
        const scoreEl = document.getElementById(scoreId);
        if (val !== null && val !== undefined) {
          scoreEl.textContent = val + '/10';
          scoreEl.className = 'progress-score ' + (val >= 8 ? 'score-high' : val >= 6 ? 'score-mid' : val >= 4 ? 'score-low' : 'score-poor');
          setTimeout(() => {
            document.getElementById(barId).style.width = (val * 10) + '%';
          }, 300);
        } else {
          scoreEl.textContent = 'No data';
          scoreEl.className = 'progress-score score-nodata';
          document.getElementById(barId).style.width = '0%';
        }
      });

      const shareText = (isRemote && annualSavings > 0)
        ? 'Moving from ' + cityName + ' to ' + countryName + ' could save me $' + annualSavings.toLocaleString() + '/year. Calculate yours: leavingamerica.co'
        : 'My $' + income.toLocaleString() + ' salary has ' + adjustedMultiplier.toFixed(1) + 'x more purchasing power in ' + countryName + '. Calculate yours: leavingamerica.co';

      if (shareBtn) {
        shareBtn.onclick = () => window.open('https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=' + encodeURIComponent(shareText));
      }

      // ── NEW JS BLOCK ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      const FLAG_MAP = {
        'AF':'🇦🇫','AL':'🇦🇱','DZ':'🇩🇿','AD':'🇦🇩','AO':'🇦🇴','AR':'🇦🇷','AM':'🇦🇲','AU':'🇦🇺','AT':'🇦🇹','AZ':'🇦🇿',
